2 Optimization algorithms – an overview

2.1 Methods that use the gradient

sq.f <- function(x) {
  nn <- length(x)
  yy <- 1:nn
  f <- sum((yy - x)^2)
  cat("Fv=", f, " at ")
  print(x)
  f
}

sq.g <- function(x) {
  nn <- length(x)
  yy <- 1:nn
  gg <- 2 * (x - yy)
}

# ls() 1 to (n-1) variant of generalized rosenbrock function
grose.f <- function(x, gs = 100) {
  n <- length(x)
  1 + sum(gs * (x[1:(n - 1)] - x[2:n]^2)^2 + (x[1:(n - 1)] - 1)^2)
}
grose.g <- function(x, gs = 100) {
  # gradient of 1 to (n-1) variant of generalized rosenbrock function # vectorized by JN 090409
  n <- length(x)
  gg <- as.vector(rep(0, n))
  tn <- 2:n
  tn1 <- tn - 1
  z1 <- x[tn1] - x[tn]^2
  z2 <- x[tn1] - 1
  gg[tn1] <- 2 * (z2 + gs * z1)
  gg[tn] <- gg[tn] - 4 * gs * z1 * x[tn]
  gg
}
x <- c(0.1, 0.8)
arksd <- stdesc(x, grose.f, grose.g, control = list(trace = 0))
print(arksd)

2.2 Newton-like methods

## Figure 2.1
F <- function(x) exp(-.05 * x) * (x - 4)^2
curve(F, from = 0, to = 5)

newt <- function(x) {
  x1 <- exp(-0.05 * x) * (2 * (x - 4)) - exp(-0.05 * x) * 0.05 * (x - 4)^2
  x2 <- (exp(-0.05 * x) * 2 - exp(-0.05 * x) * 0.05 * (2 * (x - 4)) -
    (exp(-0.05 * x) * 0.05 * (2 * (x - 4)) - exp(-0.05 * x) *
      0.05 * 0.05 * (x - 4)^2))
  xnew <- x - x1 / x2
}

x <- -9
xold <- -10
while (xold != x) {
  xold <- x
  cat("f(", x, ")=", F(x), "\n")
  x <- newt(xold)
}

newt2 <- function(x) {
  x1 <- exp(-0.05 * x) * (-8.8 + 2.4 * x - 0.05 * x^2) # f'(x) from mathematica
  x2 <- exp(-0.05 * x) * (2.84 - 0.22 * x + 0.0025 * x^2) # f''(x) from mathematica
  xnew <- x - x1 / x2
}

x <- -9
xold <- -10
while (xold != x) {
  xold <- x
  cat("f(", x, ")=", F(x), "\n")

rss <- function(par) {
  p1 <- par[1]
  p2 <- par[2]
  res <- exp(p1 * sin(p2 * xx)) - yy
  sum(res * res)
}

3.8 Providing derivatives for functions

eps <- sqrt(.Machine$double.eps)
eps
[1] 1.4901e-08
## ----label=C03gr1, echo=TRUE---------------------------------------------
gr <- function(par, ...) {
  fbase <- myfn(par, ...) # ensure we have right value, may not be necessary
  df <- rep(NA, length(par))
  teps <- eps * (abs(par) + eps)
  for (i in 1:length(par)) {
    dx <- par
    dx[i] <- dx[i] + teps[i] # Dangerous step if a constraint is in the way!
    tdf <- (myfn(dx, ...) - fbase) / teps[i]
    if (!is.finite(tdf) || is.nan(tdf)) tdf <- 0 # Is this a good choice?
    df[i] <- tdf
  }
  df
}

4.3.3 Little Polly Nomial

## ----label=C04chunk10, echo=TRUE, size="scriptsize", cache=TRUE----------
z <- c(10, -3, 0, 1)
simpol <- function(x) { # calculate polynomial z at x
  zz <- c(10, -3, 0, 1)
  ndeg <- length(zz) - 1 # degree of polynomial
  val <- zz[ndeg + 1]
  for (i in 1:ndeg) {
    val <- val * x + zz[ndeg + 1 - i]
  }
  val
}

simpol2 <- function(x) {
  10 - 3 * x + x^3

4.3.4 A hypothequial question

## ----label=C04chunk12, echo=TRUE, size="scriptsize", cache=TRUE----------
mrate <- function(R) {
  val <- 0
  den <- 1
  fact <- 1 / 6
  term <- 1
  rr <- R / 200
  repeat { # main loop
    term <- term * fact * rr / den
    vallast <- val
    val <- val + term
    #      cat("term =",term,"  val now ",val,"\n")
    if (val == vallast) break
    fact <- (fact - 1)
    den <- den + 1
    if (den > 1000) stop("Too many terms in mrate")
  }
  val * 100
}
A <- function(I, Rval) {
  A <- (1 + I / 100)^6 - (1 + R / 200)
}
Rvec <- c()
i.formula <- c()
i.root <- c()
i.mrate <- c()

eps <- .Machine$double.eps
for (r2 in 0:18) {
  R <- r2 / 2 # rate per year
  Rvec <- c(Rvec, R)
  i.formula <- c(i.formula, 100 * ((1 + R / 200)^(1 / 6) - 1))
  i.root <- c(i.root, uniroot(A, c(0, 20), Rval = R)$root) # default or
  # i.root<-c(i.root, uniroot(A,c(0,20),tol=eps,Rval=R)$root) # with tol
  i.mrate <- c(i.mrate, mrate(R))
}
tabR <- data.frame(Rvec, i.mrate, (i.formula - i.mrate), (i.root - i.mrate))
colnames(tabR) <- c("rate", "i.mrate", "form - mrate", "root - mrate")
print(tabR)

4.4 Approaches to solving 1D root-finding problems

## ----label=C04mytanchunk1, echo=TRUE, size="scriptsize", cache=TRUE------
mytan <- function(xdeg) { # tangent in degrees
  xrad <- xdeg * pi / 180.0 # conversion to radians
  tt <- tan(xrad)
}
gmytan <- function(xdeg) { # tangent in degrees
  xrad <- xdeg * pi / 180.0 # conversion to radians
  gg <- pi / (180 * cos(xrad)^2)
}
curve(mytan, from = -360, to = 360, n = 501)

curve(gmytan, from = -360, to = 360, n = 501)
